title: US tariff threats over Greenland pose 'more political than economic' consequences for Europe
subhed: From January to November 2025, European exports to the US increased by 2%, despite the tariffs implemented by the Trump administration. The impact, however, was more severe in certain subsectors, including wine.

Israeli hostages in Gaza recount sexual violence during their captivity
subhed: Over the past two years, several people held captive by Hamas and other organizations have reported suffering sexual violence in addition to deprivation, beatings, humiliation and threats.

title: Venezuela says it has received $300 million from US oil sale used to prop up currency
subhed: Delcy Rodriguez said the sum from a $500 million sale conducted by Washington would be used to 'stabilize' the foreign exchange market. Before the US capture of longtime leader Nicolas Maduro on January 3, Venezuela had been forced to offer huge discounts on its crude to circumvent the US oil embargo.

title: PSG's bid for top eight finish jeopardized after Lisbon loss
subhed: Despite being largely dominant, Paris Saint-Germain struggled to create genuine chances, their combinations around the penalty area proving too weak and predictable for the Lisbon defense. 'The result is disappointing and unfair,' said coach Luis Enrique of the 2-1 defeat.

title: Bastien François, political scientist: 'There are good and bad ways to use Article 49.3' of the French Constitution
subhed: French Prime Minister Sébastien Lecornu's decision to ram the budget through Parliament without a vote, using Article 49.3 of the Constitution, is not undemocratic, explains political science professor Bastien François.

title: The strange airborne rescue of Gaza's donkeys, from Israel to Europe
subhed: Since 2022, Sharon Cohen, who runs an animal rescue group near Tel Aviv, has removed donkeys from Palestinian owners she accuses of mistreatment and sent them to shelters across Europe. The initiative has drawn outrage amid Gaza's deepening humanitarian crisis.
